18/03/2007
GRACANICA, Serbia -- Serbs gathered on Saturday (March 17th) to commemorate the third anniversary of ethnic riots in which 19 people were killed and dozens of Orthodox churches and monasteries were destroyed or damaged. 
Separate observances were held in Belgrade and in Serbian-populated municipalities in the province. 
Serbian President Boris Tadic urged international organisations to guarantee peace and security for all Kosovo citizens and bring the perpetrators to justice. 
So far, 134 people have been convicted. 
(Politika - 18/03/07; Beta, Tanjug - 17/03/07)
